              "textEn": "A child I know and like a lot is my cousin’s son, Leo, who is eight years old. I have known him since he was a baby, of course, but I only became really close to him about two years ago. At that time, my cousin was extremely busy with work, so I often helped look after him on Saturday afternoons. To be honest, I thought it might be tiring at first, because young children can be noisy and unpredictable. However, Leo won me over almost immediately. He was full of energy, but at the same time he was warm, funny, and surprisingly thoughtful, so I quickly developed a soft spot for him.",
              "textZh": "(我認識而且很喜歡的一個小朋友，是我表姐的兒子 Leo，他現在八歲了。當然，我從他還是嬰兒的時候就認識他，不過我真正和他變得很熟，大概是兩年前的事。那時候我表姐工作非常忙，所以我常常在星期六下午幫忙照顧他。老實說，一開始我以為這會很累，因為小朋友有時會很嘈吵，也很難預料。不過，Leo 幾乎立刻就讓我很喜歡他。他精力充沛，但同時又很溫暖、很有趣，而且出乎意料地細心，所以我很快就對他特別有好感。)"
