              "textEn": "She gave it to me because she wanted to celebrate that small milestone in my life. More importantly, she said she chose a pen because it symbolised a new chapter. I remember she told me, half joking and half serious, that I was now old enough to “write my own story.” That line really struck a chord with me. At that stage of my life, I was standing at a crossroads, trying to decide what to study and what kind of person I wanted to become. So in a way, the gift felt like more than a present; it felt like a quiet vote of confidence.",
              "textZh": "（她送我這份禮物，是因為她想為我人生中的一個小里程碑慶祝一下。更重要的是，她說她選擇送一支筆，是因為它象徵一個新篇章。我記得她當時半開玩笑、半認真地對我說，我已經長大到可以「寫下自己的人生故事」了。那句話真的很打動我。那時候的我正站在人生的十字路口，努力思考自己要讀甚麼、又想成為一個怎樣的人。所以某程度上，那份禮物不只是禮物，更像是一種安靜而有力的信任。）"
