              "headingZh": "(2. 牠是甚麼樣子，以及有甚麼地方吸引了我（過去）)",
              "textEn": "What struck me first was the way it moved. It did not rush or panic. Instead, it glided through the water as if it had all the time in the world. Its movements were slow, smooth, and graceful, and that made it stand out from the other sea creatures around it. I remember the greenish shell, the gentle eyes, and the quiet rhythm of its body as it disappeared into the blue water. What impressed me most was its silence, because it seemed completely at home there. It was not doing anything dramatic, but that was exactly what made it so fascinating.",
              "textZh": "(最先吸引我的，是牠游動的方式。牠完全沒有急躁或慌張。相反，牠在水中滑行的樣子，就好像牠擁有世界上所有的時間一樣。牠的動作緩慢、流暢，而且優雅，所以在周圍其他海洋生物之中顯得特別突出。我仍然記得牠帶點綠色的龜殼、溫和的眼神，以及牠消失在藍色海水中時那種安靜的節奏。最令我印象深刻的是牠的寧靜，因為牠看起來完全屬於那個地方。牠並沒有做甚麼特別戲劇化的事，但正正因為如此，牠才顯得格外迷人。)"
