              "textEn": "A painting I would really love to have in my home is one of Claude Monet’s Water Lilies paintings, or at least a large, high-quality reproduction of it. I first came across it when I was in secondary school, because it appeared in an art book in the library. At that age, I did not know much about painting, but that image stayed with me. Unlike dramatic or heavy paintings, it felt gentle and almost dreamlike, as if the surface of the water were breathing.",
              "textZh": "(我很想放在家中的一幅畫，是 Claude Monet 的《Water Lilies》系列其中一幅，或者至少是一幅高品質、大尺寸的複製品。我最初接觸它，是在中學的時候，因為我在圖書館的一本藝術書裡看到了它。那個年紀的我其實不太懂畫，但那個畫面卻一直留在我腦海裡。跟一些很戲劇化或者很沉重的畫相比，它給人的感覺很溫柔，也有一種近乎夢境般的氣氛，好像水面本身正在呼吸一樣。)"
