              "textEn": "A book I read recently was The Midnight Library, which was recommended to me by one of my close friends. She actually gave it to me as a birthday present last summer because she said it seemed like my kind of book. By that, she meant something reflective, slightly emotional, and thought-provoking without being too difficult to read. At that time, I had been feeling quite drained from work, so I was looking for something that could pull me in without feeling like hard labour. That is exactly why I picked it up almost straight away.",
              "textZh": "（我最近讀的一本書是《The Midnight Library》，這本書是我一位好朋友推薦給我的。其實它是她去年夏天送給我的生日禮物，因為她說這本書感覺很像我會喜歡的類型。她的意思是，這本書有反思性，帶一點情感，也很發人深省，但又不會難讀得讓人有壓力。那段時間我工作上有點心力交瘁，所以我很想找一本既能吸引我讀下去、又不會像做苦工一樣的書。正因如此，我幾乎一拿到手就開始看了。）"
