              "textEn": "It took me about a week to finish it, although I did not read it in one go. I usually read a few chapters each night before going to bed, so it became part of my routine for several days. In terms of genre, I would describe it as a mix of fiction, fantasy, and philosophical drama. The story centres on a woman who finds herself in a mysterious library between life and death, and each book on the shelves allows her to step into a different version of her life. On the surface, it sounds like quite an unusual concept, but the emotions in it are very real, so it never feels distant or confusing.",
              "textZh": "（我大概花了一個星期把它讀完，不過我並不是一口氣讀完的。我通常每晚睡前看幾章，所以有好幾天它都成了我日常生活的一部分。如果要說它的類型，我會形容它是小說、奇幻，以及帶有哲思色彩的故事的結合。這本書講的是一位女性，她發現自己置身於一間介乎生與死之間的神秘圖書館，而書架上的每一本書都可以讓她走進自己人生的另一種版本。乍聽之下，這個概念好像很不尋常，但它裡面的情感其實非常真實，所以讀起來一點也不會覺得遙遠或難以理解。）"
