              "headingZh": "",
              "textEn": "One positive change in my life was learning how to manage my time properly and becoming a much more organised person. This change happened during my second year at university, when I was constantly overwhelmed by deadlines, group projects, and part-time work. Before that, I used to live from one deadline to the next. I was always racing against the clock, leaving things until the last minute, and telling myself that I worked best under pressure. To be honest, that sounded better in theory than in practice, because in reality I was stressed, exhausted, and rarely satisfied with my work.",
              "textZh": "（我人生中其中一個很正面的改變，就是學會了真正管理好自己的時間，並且成為一個有條理得多的人。這個改變發生在我大學二年級的時候，當時我經常被截止日期、小組功課和兼職工作壓得喘不過氣來。在那之前，我的生活方式基本上就是一個截止日期接一個截止日期。我總是在和時間賽跑，經常把事情拖到最後一刻，還會跟自己說我是在壓力下表現最好的人。老實說，這個說法聽起來比實際情況美好得多，因為現實是我總是很大壓力、很疲累，而且對自己的表現也很少真正滿意。）"
