              "textEn": "One of the things I loved most about Kyoto was its famous attractions. For example, I visited Fushimi Inari Shrine, which is well known for its long path of bright red torii gates. Walking through them felt almost like stepping into another world. I also went to Kiyomizu-dera, where I could enjoy an amazing view of the city, especially in the late afternoon when the sunlight turned everything golden. Another memorable place was Arashiyama Bamboo Grove. The tall bamboo swayed gently in the wind, and the whole area felt calm and almost dreamlike. On top of that, the Gion district was fascinating because it preserved a traditional side of Japan that is hard to find elsewhere.",
              "textZh": "（我最喜歡京都的一點，就是它有很多著名景點。例如，我去了伏見稻荷大社，那裡最有名的就是一整條由鮮紅色鳥居組成的路。走在其中，感覺幾乎就像進入了另一個世界。我也去了清水寺，從那裡可以看到非常美的城市景色，尤其是在傍晚時分，陽光把周圍一切都染成金色。另一個令我印象深刻的地方是嵐山竹林。高高的竹子在風中輕輕搖動，整個地方都讓人覺得平靜，甚至有點像夢境一樣。除此之外，祇園也非常吸引，因為它保留了一種在其他地方很難找到的日本傳統風貌。）"
