              "textEn": "I liked Kyoto not only because it was visually beautiful, but also because of the atmosphere. Some cities impress you with noise, energy, and speed, but Kyoto won me over in a quieter way. It felt like a city that never needed to shout to be noticed. I loved the balance between history and daily life. You could see ancient temples, narrow streets, traditional houses, and at the same time ordinary people simply going about their day. To me, that made the city feel authentic rather than overly commercial.",
              "textZh": "（我喜歡京都，不只是因為它外表很美，還因為它整體的氛圍。有些城市是靠熱鬧、活力和節奏感令人印象深刻，但京都是用一種更安靜的方式打動我的。它給我的感覺就像是一座根本不需要大聲張揚，也自然會被人注意到的城市。我很喜歡它在歷史感和日常生活之間取得的平衡。你可以看到古老的寺廟、狹窄的小街、傳統的房屋，同時也能看到普通人自然地過著他們的日常生活。對我來說，這令整座城市顯得真實，而不是過度商業化。）"
