              "textEn": "What I usually do is traditional. Before the festival, my family cleans the flat, buys snacks, and puts up red couplets and paper decorations. On the first day, we visit relatives, share a big meal, and exchange blessings for the year ahead. I especially like the dinner, because the table is always full of symbolic dishes, and the whole evening feels busy in the best possible way. It is one of the few times when everyone slows down and shows up.",
              "textZh": "（我通常會做的事情都比較傳統。節日前，我家人會一起打掃家裡、買年貨，還會貼揮春和紙裝飾。到年初一，我們會去探親、一起吃一頓豐盛的飯，並互相送上新一年的祝福。我特別喜歡年夜飯，因為桌上總是擺滿有象徵意義的菜式，而整個晚上都帶著一種忙碌卻很美好的感覺。這也是少數一個所有人都會慢下來、真正出現的時候。）"
