              "textEn": "The reason I like this festival so much is not just the celebration itself, but the feeling behind it. It carries a sense of renewal, gratitude, and connection. After a long year of routines and pressure, it still feels like pressing a reset button. I also enjoy the contrast between the noise outside and the warmth at home. Firecrackers, bright colours, laughter, and long conversations make everything feel more vivid, almost as if ordinary life has been given a brighter frame.",
              "textZh": "（我這麼喜歡這個節日，原因不只是慶祝本身，而是它背後的感覺。它帶著一種更新、感恩和連結的意味。經過一整年規律而有壓力的生活之後，它仍然像是按下了一個重新開始的按鈕。我也很喜歡外面熱鬧聲響和家中溫暖感覺之間的對比。爆竹聲、鮮明的顏色、笑聲，以及長長的交談，都令一切變得更鮮活，就好像平凡生活被加上了一個更明亮的框架。）"
