          "responses": [
            {
              "number": 1,
              "headingEn": "1. Opening: what it is",
              "headingZh": "（1. 開場：它是甚麼）",
              "textEn": "One product that is strongly associated with Hong Kong is Hong Kong-style milk tea. It is a dark, smooth tea drink usually served hot or iced in cafés called cha chaan tengs. People mainly drink it with breakfast or afternoon tea, but many also order it as a daily comfort drink. Although it sounds simple, it has quite a distinctive character. In Hong Kong, it is more than just a beverage. In a way, it is almost woven into life.",
              "textZh": "（我想講的一樣很能代表香港的產品，就是港式奶茶。它是一種深色、順滑的茶飲，通常會在茶餐廳裡以熱飲或凍飲的形式供應。人們主要會在早餐或下午茶時喝它，但也有很多人會把它當成每天都想喝的安慰飲品。雖然它聽起來很簡單，但其實它很有自己的特色。在香港，它不只是一杯飲品。某程度上，它幾乎已經融入了日常生活。）"
            },
            {
              "number": 2,
              "headingEn": "2. What it is used for",
              "headingZh": "（2. 它是用來做甚麼的）",
              "textEn": "It is used partly to wake people up, but also to bring people together. Office workers grab it before work, students drink it during lunch, and older customers sip it while reading the newspaper. What makes it special is the balance between strength and softness. The tea itself is bold and slightly bitter, while the evaporated milk makes it richer and silkier. That contrast gives it a flavor that feels both energetic and comforting at the time for people.",
              "textZh": "（它一方面是用來提神的，但另一方面也有讓人聚在一起的作用。上班族會在上班前買一杯，學生會在午餐時喝，而年長一點的客人則會一邊看報紙，一邊慢慢喝。它特別的地方，在於它在濃烈與柔和之間取得了平衡。茶本身味道較濃，也帶一點苦味，而淡奶則令它變得更香濃、更順滑。這種對比令它同時給人一種有精神和有安慰感的味道。）"
            },
            {
              "number": 3,
              "headingEn": "3. How it is made or produced",
              "headingZh": "（3. 它是怎樣製作或生產的）",
              "textEn": "As for how it is made, the process is more careful than many people expect. Tea leaves are brewed through a cloth filter, often several times, to create a strong and smooth base. After that, evaporated milk and sugar are added in the right proportion. Good milk tea is not thrown together casually; it is built with patience and consistency. Even a small difference in timing can change the final taste, which is why experienced tea makers are valued highly.",
              "textZh": "（至於它是怎樣製作的，整個過程其實比很多人想像中更講究。茶葉會透過布袋過濾，通常還會重複沖泡幾次，目的是做出一個濃而順滑的茶底。之後，再按合適比例加入淡奶和糖。好的奶茶不是隨便混合就可以做出來的；它是靠耐性和穩定度慢慢建立出來的。哪怕只是時間上有一點點差異，也會改變最後的味道，這也是為甚麼有經驗的沖茶師傅會被高度重視。）"
            },
            {
              "number": 4,
              "headingEn": "4. Why my country produces it",
              "headingZh": "（4. 為甚麼我的地方會生產它）",
              "textEn": "I think Hong Kong produces this drink because it reflects the city itself. It is fast but refined, humble but memorable, and shaped by a mix of Eastern and Western influences. It suits a place where people live busy lives but still care about flavor and ritual. That is why I think it will remain popular for a long time. Compared with other drinks, it carries real identity. To me, it is famous because it turns a habit into culture.",
              "textZh": "（我覺得香港會生產這種飲品，是因為它很能反映這座城市本身。它節奏快，但又講究；它平凡，卻令人難忘，而且它的形成也深深受到中西文化交融的影響。它很適合一個生活節奏很快、但人們仍然重視味道和儀式感的地方。正因如此，我相信它在很長一段時間內都會繼續受歡迎。和很多其他飲品相比，它有更鮮明的身份感。對我來說，它之所以出名，是因為它把一個日常習慣變成了一種文化。）"
            }
          ]
