              "textEn": "In terms of content, the book follows a pilot who crashes in the desert and meets a strange little prince from another planet. On the surface, it is a simple story, but underneath it explores friendship, loneliness, love, and the way adults often lose sight of what really matters. What I admire most is that the book says profound things in a very light voice. It never lectures the reader, yet it leaves a surprisingly strong emotional echo long afterwards.",
              "textZh": "（內容方面，這本書講述一位飛行員在沙漠墜機後，遇到一位來自另一個星球的小王子。表面上，它是一個很簡單的故事，但在底下它其實探討了友誼、孤獨、愛，以及成年人常常如何失去對真正重要事物的感覺。我最欣賞的一點，是這本書用一種非常輕柔的聲音說出很深刻的話。它從不對讀者說教，但讀完之後卻會留下很強的情感餘韻。）"
