              "textEn": "A restaurant I often go to is a café called Green Corner, near the MTR station in my neighbourhood. I first went there about two years ago with a friend who recommended it, and since then it has become one of my regular places. It is not in a fancy area, but it is easy to reach and convenient. Because it is tucked away on a quieter street, it feels like an escape from the rush of the city.",
