              "textEn": "One traffic rule I know well is the rule that drivers must stop at a red light and must not cross the junction until the signal turns green. It sounds basic, but it is one of the clearest and most important road rules in daily life. I chose this one because almost everyone, whether they drive, cycle, or walk, understands its purpose immediately. In a way, it is a small rule that carries a very heavy responsibility on busy roads.",
              "textZh": "（我很清楚知道的一條交通規則，就是駕駛者在紅燈時必須停車，而且在號誌轉綠之前不可以越過路口。這聽起來很基本，但它其實是日常生活中最清楚、也最重要的道路規則之一。我選這一條，是因為幾乎所有人，不論是駕車、踩單車，還是步行，都能立刻明白它的作用。某程度上來說，這是一條很小的規則，卻肩負著非常沉重的責任，尤其是在繁忙的道路上。）"
