              "textEn": "The best teacher I have ever had was my secondary school English teacher, Ms Wong. She taught me when I was in Form Four and Form Five, so I studied with her for about two years. Before meeting her, I saw English mainly as an exam subject. However, she changed that completely. She made the language feel alive, useful, and connected to the real world, rather than just something hidden inside textbooks, grammar drills, and endless worksheets.",
              "textZh": "(我遇過最好的一位老師，是我中學時期的英文老師王老師。她在我讀中四和中五的時候教我，所以我跟她學習了大約兩年。在認識她之前，我一直把英文主要視為一門考試科目。不過，她徹底改變了這一點。她令這門語言變得有生命、有用途，而且和真實世界連結起來，而不再只是一些藏在課本、文法練習和無止境工作紙裡的東西。)"
