              "textEn": "To get that job, I would probably need a university degree in urban planning, geography, architecture, or a related field. Besides formal qualifications, I think practical experience would matter a lot. Internships, research projects, and some understanding of transport, housing policy, and environmental issues would all be useful. Strong communication skills are also essential, because planners have to explain ideas clearly and listen to different groups of people. In other words, the job requires both technical knowledge and human understanding.",
