              "textEn": "One good law I would like to talk about is the rule that drivers and passengers must wear seat belts in cars. I first became aware of it when I was a child, because my parents would never let the car move until everyone had buckled up properly. At that time, it felt like a small routine rather than a law. However, as I got older, I understood that this simple rule exists for a very serious reason indeed today.",
              "textZh": "（我想談的一條好法律，就是司機和乘客在車裡都必須繫上安全帶的規定。我小時候就開始留意到它，因為我父母以前從來不會讓車子開動，除非所有人都已經好好繫上安全帶。那時候，它給我的感覺比較像一個小小的日常習慣，而不是一條法律。不過，當我長大之後，我開始明白，這條簡單的規定其實是為了一個非常嚴肅的原因而存在。）"
