              "textEn": "I know about her not only because she taught me for two years, but also because I watched the way she treated people every day. She was the kind of teacher who remembered students' weaknesses without making them feel small. Outside lessons, she stayed after school to answer questions, gave extra feedback on writing, and encouraged shy students to speak. In short, her job was teaching, but her real work was building confidence in other people.",
              "textZh": "（我之所以了解她，不只是因為她教了我兩年，更因為我每天都看見她怎樣對待別人。她是那種會記得學生弱點、卻不會令人感到自卑的老師。課堂以外，她會留在學校回答問題，會額外給寫作意見，也會鼓勵那些害羞的學生開口說話。簡單來說，她表面上的工作是教書，但她真正做的，其實是在建立別人的自信。）"
