              "textEn": "One job I would not like to do is emergency room nursing in a large public hospital. I first learned how demanding it is through my cousin, who has worked in healthcare for several years and often talks about night shifts, critical cases, and emotional pressure. Before hearing her stories, I assumed it was simply a medical job like many others. Later, I understood that it is a role where speed, accuracy, and emotional control are tested almost every hour.",
              "textZh": "（我不想做的一份工作，是大型公立醫院急症室的護士。我最初知道這份工作有多辛苦，是透過我的表姐，因為她在醫療行業工作了好幾年，並且常常提到夜班、危急個案，以及情緒壓力。在聽她的故事之前，我原本以為那只是一份和其他很多工作差不多的醫療職業。後來我才明白，這是一個幾乎每小時都在考驗速度、準確度和情緒控制的角色。）"
